<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 3:24PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Gilmer, northeastern
Murray and northwestern Fannin Counties through 400 PM EDT...
At 324 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Conasauga Lake, or 11
miles east of Chatsworth, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ellijay, Blue Ridge, East Ellijay, Morganton, Conasauga Lake, Jones
Mill, Cherry Log, Mountaintown, Higdon and Colwell.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
